item.title: CVE-2019-5297|2024-08-04T19:54:53.218Z -- huawei -- emily-l29c
item.description: Emily-L29C Huawei phones versions earlier than 9.0.0.159 (C185E2R1P12T8) have a Factory Reset Protection (FRP) bypass security vulnerability. Before the FRP account is verified and activated during the reset process, the attacker can perform some special operations to bypass the FRP function and obtain the right to use the mobile phone.

item.title: CVE-2019-5236|2024-08-04T19:47:56.831Z -- huawei -- emily-l29c
item.description: Huawei smart phones Emily-L29C with versions of 8.1.0.132a(C432), 8.1.0.135(C782), 8.1.0.154(C10), 8.1.0.154(C461), 8.1.0.154(C635), 8.1.0.156(C185), 8.1.0.156(C605), 8.1.0.159(C636) have a double free vulnerability. An attacker can trick a user to click a URL to exploit this vulnerability. Successful exploitation may cause the affected phone abnormal.
